Introduction¶

In this document there will be statistical analysis of Exercises table. Exercises table has 19 variables (columns) and 483 records. For the analysis below libraries will be used:

  • pandas
  • numpy
  • statistics
  • matplotlib.pyplot
  • seaborn
  • pingouin
  • distfit

Below there are information about this dataset (summary info and glimpse of data).

Columns

  • user_id,
  • code_name,
  • name_es,
  • description_es,
  • auto_generated,
  • priority_order,
  • next_program_id

will be dropped, they won't be useful in the analysis.

Variables taken into consideration are

  • created_at, updated_at,
  • pro - is the program only for pro users,
  • available - is the program available to use,
  • strength, endurance, technique, flexibility, intensity - is is on a 1-5 scale, an indication of the difficulty of the program to show users what they were choosing,
  • name_en - name of the program in English,
  • description_en - description of the program in English.

The non-NULL counts, types and glimpse of reduced data are given below.

Numerical variables¶

Variables

  • strength,
  • endurance,
  • technique,
  • flexibility and
  • intensity

are the only ones that may be considered as numerical variables.

In this section, the normal distribution evaluation will be done. For this purpose, there will be histogram, qqplot and Shapiro-Wilk test done. Below there is a histogram for numeric variables.

There is no normality in the data (from histograms, qqplots and Shapiro-Wilk tets) and kurtosis and skewness also confirms it.

Data distribution evaluation¶

In this section, data distribution will be checked (or the closest one). The criterion of determination for best fit is RSS (residual sum of squares). The RSS describes the deviation predicted from actual empirical values of data.

  • strength - the most fitting distribution is Wald (RSS = 25.1), then beta (RSS = 28,72), Pearson (RSS = 32.62), half generalized normal (RSS = 32.67) and exponentially normal (RSS = 47.08). The RSS value is very big even with the best fitted distribution.

[distfit] >[pearson3   ] [0.11 sec] [RSS: 32.6243] [loc=0.181 scale=0.208]

There are 456 (94%) programs for pro users. Only 42 (9%) programs are available. Most of the programs had strength, endurance, technique, flexibility and intensity at level 0 - 443 (92% each). For strength 3 programs had level 1 (1%), 5 programs had level 2 (1%), 16 programs had level 3 (3%), 5 programs had level 4 (1%) and 11 programs had level 5 (2%). For intensity 13 programs had level 2 (3%), 5 programs had level 3 (1%), 10 programs had level 4 (2%), 12 programs had level 5 (2%) and there was no programs for level 1.
